"{\"uid\": \"breitbart.com-entertainment-2024-07-31-rob-schneider-boycotts-olympics-over-drag-queen-last-supper-openly-celebrates-satan\", \"text\": \"Actor-comedian andSaturday Night Livealum Rob\\u00a0Schneider is boycotting the Paris Olympics over its opening ceremony - which involved a parody of the Last Supper featuring drag queens - saying the anti-Christian performance \\\"openly celebrates Satan.\\\"  \\\"I am sorry to say to ALL the world's GREATEST ATHLETES, I wish you ALL THE BEST, but I cannot watch an Olympics that disrespects Christianity and openly celebrates Satan,\\\"\\u00a0Schneider said in a Sunday X post. \\\"I\\u00a0sincerely hope THESE @Olympics get the same amount of viewers as @cspan.\\\"  \\\"Guys with their genitalia hanging out in front of children?! Drag Queens?! I wasn't sure if I was watching the @Olympics or if I was watching a school board meeting\\u2026\\\" theDeuce Bigalowstar added in another X post.  Schneider is not the only celebrity to blast the Last Supper parody featured at this year's\\u00a0Olympic games.  Actress Candace Cameron Burereactedto the Paris Olympics opening ceremony by calling it \\\"disgusting,\\\" adding, \\\"It made me so sad.\\\"  \\\"To\\u00a0watch such an incredible and wonderful event that's gonna take place over the next two weeks, and see the opening ceremonies completely blaspheme and mock the Christian faith with their interpretation of the Last Supper was disgusting, and it made me so sad,\\\" theFull Housestar said.  Watch Below:    A post shared by Candace Cameron Bure (@candacecbure)  As Breitbart Newsreported, French bishops have also released a statement expressing their dismay over the anti-Christian parody of the Last Supper, referring to the Paris Olympics opening ceremony as a performance that featured \\\"scenes of derision and mockery of Christianity.\\\"  First lady Jill Biden, meanwhile,praisedthe anti-Christian parody, calling it \\\"spectacular.\\\"  On Sunday, organizers for the Paris Olympicsissued an apologyto those who were left offended by the LGBTQ parody, saying they \\\"wanted to\\u00a0send a message of love\\\" and\\u00a0inclusion, and did not have intentions \\\"to be subversive.\\\"  \\\"My wish is not to be subversive, nor to mock or to shock,\\\"\\u00a0Thomas Jolly, the artistic director for the Olympics opening ceremony,toldthe Associated Press. \\\"Most of all,\\u00a0I wanted to send a message of love, a message of inclusion and not at all to divide.\\\"  You canfollow Alana\\u00a0Mastrangelo onFacebookand X at@ARmastrangelo, and onInstagram.  Pleaselet us knowif you are having issues with commenting.          Copyright \\u00a9 2025 Breitbart\"}"